{{Infobox medical intervention|Name=自我照顧|image=Walking for Health in Epsom-5Aug2009 (3).jpg|caption=散步對健康有益|ICD10=|ICD9unlinked=|MeshID=D012648|OPS301=|OtherCodes=}} '''自我照顧'''是在[[健康照護|健康照護]]中的術語，是指在[[個體|個體]]控制下的、有意识的、自发的任何必要的人的调节功能。<ref name="hacs">{{Cite book|title=Exploring the Correlates of Self Provided Health Care Behaviour|editor-last=Coburn|editor-first=David|last=Alexander Segall|last2=Jay Goldstein|editor2-first=Alex|editor2-last=D'Arcy|editor3-first=George Murray|editor3-last=Torrance|year=1998|publisher=University of Toronto Press|isbn=978-0-8020-8052-3|pages=279–280|chapterurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=AZ4o0TI5LqwC|accessdate=2013-08-29}}</ref> 

一些人認爲自我照顧和由健康照護業者照顧是對立的，<ref name="ssc">{{Cite book|title=Supporting Self Care in Primary Care|last=Chambers|first=Ruth|last2=Gill Wakley|last3=Alison Blenkinsopp|year=2006|publisher=Radcliffe Publishing|isbn=978-1-84619-070-4|pages=15, 101, 105|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6zR6yy-5wzsC|accessdate=2013-08-29}}</ref>但一些人認爲兩者有更複雜的關係。<ref name=":8">{{Cite journal|title=A Middle-Range Theory of Self-Care of Chronic Illness|last=Riegel|first=Barbara|last2=Jaarsma|first2=Tiny|date=2012|journal=Advances in Nursing Science|issue=3|doi=10.1097/ANS.0b013e318261b1ba|volume=35|pages=194–204|issn=0161-9268|pmid=22739426|last3=Strömberg|first3=Anna}}</ref>在現代醫學中，[[預防醫學|預防醫學]]與自我照顧最接近。不遵醫囑和[[精神疾患|精神疾患]]會讓自我照顧更難進行。<ref name="nugu">{{Cite book|title=Nurses' Guide to Teaching Diabetes Self-management|last=Mertig|first=Rita G.|year=2012|publisher=Springer Publishing Company|isbn=978-0-8261-0828-9|page=240|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=oUT5JKmrdgYC|accessdate=2013-08-30}}</ref> 很多人認爲解决全球医疗费用上涨的辦法就有自我照顧，而費用則由政府支持。自我照顧是卫生和社会保健的支柱，这一概念意味着现代[[醫療系統|医疗系統]]的一个重要组成部分受[[委任立法|委任立法]]的约束。<ref name="nuth">{{Cite book|title=The Concept of Self Care|last=Kollack|first=Ingrid|editor-first=Hesook Suzie|editor-last=Kim|editor2-first=Ingrid|editor2-last=Kollak|year=2006|publisher=Springer Publishing Company|isbn=978-0-8261-4006-7|page=45|chapterurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=OY1OT_0vDaEC|accessdate=2013-08-31}}</ref>

自我照顧被认为是慢性病患者的一种主要护理方式，这些患者会做出许多日常决定來自我管理[[疾病|疾病]]。<ref name="dx.doi.org">{{Cite journal|title=PAtient self-management of chronic disease in primary care|last=Bodenheimer|first=Thomas|date=2002-11-20|journal=JAMA|issue=19|doi=10.1001/jama.288.19.2469|volume=288|pages=2469–2475|issn=0098-7484|pmid=12435261}}</ref><ref name=":8"/> 自我管理是十分關鍵的，而且自我管理教育是对[[初級照護|初級照護]]患者傳統教育的补充，以使在患有慢性病時尽可能提高生活质量。<ref name="hacs"/>自我保健是需學習、有目的且持续性的。<ref name="scs">{{Cite book|title=Self-care Science, Nursing Theory, and Evidence-based Practice|last=Taylor|first=Susan G.|last2=Katherine Renpenning|last3=Kathie McLaughlin Renpenning|year=2011|publisher=Springer Publishing Company|isbn=978-0-8261-0779-4|pages=39–41|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=alHquhnlbHwC|accessdate=2013-08-25}}</ref>

== 必需 ==
有許多自我照顧的方式適用於所有年齡的人并且是基本人类需求所必需的。<ref name="scs"/> 例如，人類需要摄入足够的空气，水和食物。在[[糞便|排便]]和排泄过程中也需要注意。[[睡眠|睡眠]]与活动，孤独与社交中必须保持平衡。 预防和避免人为造成危险以及参与社会团体也是必須的。[[心理成熟|心理成熟]]需要履行自我照顾职责。 <ref name="scepashc">{{Cite book|title=Self-care: Embodiment, Personal Autonomy and the Shaping of Health Consciousness|last=Ziguras|first=Christopher|year=2013|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-134-41969-2|pages=14–15|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CksXt89K-6QC|accessdate=2013-08-31}}</ref> 

